Privacy Policy for DayPilot
Effective Date: 12/27/2025
DayPilot respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is handled when you use the DayPilot app.

Information We Collect
DayPilot does not collect, sell, or share personal information.
The app stores only the information you choose to provide, including:
Task titles
Notes
Categories
Due dates and reminders
This data is used solely to provide the app’s functionality.

Data Storage
Your data is stored:
Locally on your device
In your personal iCloud account (if iCloud is enabled)
DayPilot uses Apple’s CloudKit framework. Your data is:
Encrypted
Accessible only to you
Not visible to the developer or any third party

Voice & Siri Features
DayPilot supports:
Siri shortcuts
Voice dictation for tasks and notes
Voice input is processed by Apple using system services. DayPilot:
Does not record or store voice data
Does not transmit audio to any external servers

Notifications
If you enable reminders, DayPilot uses local notifications to alert you about tasks. Notification permissions can be changed at any time in iOS Settings.

Third-Party Services
DayPilot relies only on Apple system services, including:
iCloud / CloudKit
Siri
Local Notifications
No third-party analytics, tracking, or advertising services are used.

Data Sharing
DayPilot does not:
Share your data
Sell your data
Track you across apps or websites

Your Control
You have full control over your data:
Delete tasks at any time
Disable iCloud syncing
Remove the app to delete all local data

Children’s Privacy
DayPilot does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

Changes to This Policy
This policy may be updated occasionally. Any changes will be reflected with a new effective date.

Contact
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:
Developer: Matt Harris Email: matt.harris9@yahoo.com
